    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-11-12T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-11-12T19:00:00-05:00" n="188"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d188">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Conference/230: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-13T00:00:00+00:00"
                            >November 13, 1937—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received November 14—9:45
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>31. The draft declaration referred to in my 30, November 13, 4 p.m. was submitted
                    to the Conference this afternoon. After considerable discussion participated in
                    by practically all of the delegates <pb facs="0191" n="183" xml:id="pg_183"/>
                    and after numerous amendments it was accepted (except by Italy) although final
                    passage was delayed until Monday at the request of Sweden, Norway, and Denmark
                    which asked for time to consult their Governments. Italy argued in favor of
                    delay before passing the declaration but gained no support largely because
                    Aldrovandi declared that Italy would probably in any event refrain from
                    accepting it either in whole or in part.</p>
                <p>Two points only in connection with the declaration seem to require comment:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>(1st). Due to widespread opposition to specifically expressing the hope
                            that Japan would still see fit to accept the tender of good offices it
                            was necessary to accept the modified form found at the beginning of the
                            last paragraph; and (2d) the last paragraph should be read in the light
                            of our decision to adopt a further declaration of common attitude before
                            taking a recess either the end of next week or the beginning of the
                            following week.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Text follows. [Here follows text; for declaration adopted November 15, see <ref
                        target="frus1931-41v01#pg_410">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, volume I, page
                        410</ref>.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
